# OpenClaw — the one shared local-LLM model alias for all of my apps.
#
# Apps never name a raw Ollama model (qwen3.5:4b, etc.) directly. They all ask
# for "openclaw", and this file decides what that actually is. Swap the FROM
# line, re-run ./install.sh, and every app moves together — with one copy of the
# weights resident in RAM instead of each app loading its own.
#
# Current pick: qwen3:4b (Q4_K_M, ~2.5 GB). Reasoning model — callers should
# send "think": false per-request (Ollama has no Modelfile-level switch yet;
# see FOR-AGENTS.md).
#
# NOTE (2026-07-04): on this Jetson, qwen3:4b currently OOMs on load
# (cudaMalloc ~2.5 GB fails). The largest model observed to load here is
# ~1.9 GB. This is set as the default by explicit operator decision; getting
# it to actually load needs a memory-reservation fix on the host (device-tree
# carveouts / CMA), not a Modelfile change.
FROM qwen3:4b

# Qwen3 non-thinking sampling params.
PARAMETER temperature 0.7
PARAMETER top_p 0.8
PARAMETER top_k 20
PARAMETER min_p 0

# Match the server runtime (-c 4096). Keep callers' prompt theirs.
PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
